<br>
But, Here is a Situation I will give you.<br>
<br>
Auno is one of our enchanters, We are in Hate, He casts Mez on a Cleric of Innorok. Resists, Now as we have it set up now, Auno does not die, Because our clerics, druids, and shamans are good enuff players where they keep him alive no matter what. Auno is Neutral but it wouldnt matters, But if he was evil and we had good clerics, he wouldnt be getting a heal from them, or the good cleric couldnt res him. Its just alot of BS that makes my job, as Raid leader, That much harder. Frankly it just adds another headache to the ones I have.<br>
<br>
Planning groups for raids, Making sure the groups are set up right isnt as easy as it sounds and just to add another degree of difficulty to this would just prolong the raid start and make me pull my hair out.<br>
<br>
Our guild doesnt need much  more than we have to accomplish stuff in this game except maybe the few very biggest mobs in game, example avatar of War. we have 38 active members who raid on a regualar basis in all different time zones, have at least 10 people on at all times(usually). Our raid attendance is usually from 22-30 people, and because of this, Just adding a *team* of goods, would do more harm then good. Pretty much cause you havent raided with us, Know our habits, and would lack the nessesary teamwork we need to make raids run right. FaF is a type of guild that believes tactics, organization, and stragedy over numbers. And right now, If a *good team* comes up to where they are Level to Raid what we are raiding , Then Im sorry but they are just out of luck.<br>
<br>
I am a strait forward guy, and I think this post deserved a strait forward answer. If i offended anyone at all i am truely sorry, but i believe in telling ya like it is, so there is no miscomunications. Thank you. <p>Bako Emberfist<BR>
